HEADWORD: Annuity
<hw>An*nu"i*ty</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Annuities</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[LL.
<ets>annuitas</ets>, fr. L. <ets>annus</ets> year: cf. F.
<ets>annuit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <def>A sum of money, payable yearly,
to continue for a given number of years, for life, or forever; an annual
allowance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

